Founded on 22 July 2015,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://feministphilosophers.wordpress.com/2015/07/22/feminist-philosophy-quarterly-launched/ |title=Feminist Philosophy Quarterly, launched |last=Norlock |first= Kate|date=22 July 2015 |website=Feminist Philosophers |publisher= |access-date= 26 November 2017 |quote=}} </ref> '''Feminist Philosophy Quarterly''' (FPQ) is an online, [[open access]], [[peer-reviewed]] journal dedicated to promoting feminist philosophical scholarship.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Robeyns|first1=Ingrid|title=Feminist Philosophy – Open Access resources|url=http://crookedtimber.org/2016/03/08/feminist-philosophy-open-access-resources/|website=Crooked Timber|accessdate=2017-11-09}}</ref> The journal is published quarterly and strives to include and incorporate the entirety of [[feminist philosophy]] across the world and including different traditions. The editors-in-chief are [[Samantha Brennan]], [[Carla Fehr]], Alice MacLachlan,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alicemaclachlan.com |title= Alice MacLachlan |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date=26 November 2017 |quote=}}</ref> and [[Kathryn Norlock]]; Brennan also served as a co-founder of the journal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dailynous.com/2017/07/28/brennan-western-guelph/ |title=Brennan from Western to Guelph|last=Weinberg |first=Justin |date=28 July 2017 |website=Daily Nous |publisher= |access-date= 26 November 2017 |quote=}} </ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.universityaffairs.ca/news/people-on-the-move/announcements-september-2017/|title=Announcements – September 2017 {{!}} University Affairs|work=University Affairs|access-date=2018-08-23|language=en-US}}</ref>
The journal aims to enhance feminist philosophers' and women's position in the philosophical sphere and the world at large, as well as being a platform for philosophical research that engages the issues faced by wider society. FPQ prioritises aligning itself with people who work towards fighting oppression and achieving equality and fairness.<ref name="IAPH">{{cite web |url=http://www.women-philosophy.org/portfolio/new-journal-feminist-philosophy-quarterly/ |title=New Journal: Feminist Philosophy Quarterly |last= |first= |date=28 February 2014 |website= IAPh – Women Philosophy |publisher= |access-date= 26 November 2017 |quote=}}</ref>
Taking issues of bias in publication seriously, FPQ has a triple-anonymous review policy. This means that authors, editors, and reviewers are all anonymous to one another. In addition to publishing peer reviewed scholarly articles, the journal also publishes a variety of invited and submitted symposia.
FPQ's online platform is hosted by [[Digital Commons]] (powered by [[bepress]]) at Scholarship at Western, in turn by [[University of Western Ontario|Western University]].
