{{Infobox Korean name |img= |title=Jeong Hyeon-jo |caption= |hangul=정현조 |hanja=鄭顯祖 |rr=Jeong Hyeon-jo |mr=Chŏng Hyŏn-jo |hangulja=효중 |hanjaja=孝仲 |rrja=Hyojung |mrja=Hyojung |hangulph=편정 |hanjaph=褊玎 |rrph=Pyeonjeong |mrph=P'yŏnjŏng }} '''Jeong Hyeon-jo''' ([[korea]]n:정현조, [[hanja]]:鄭顯組, 1440&ndash;1504) was a politician and writer during [[Korea]]'s [[Joseon Dynasty]]. He was the younger son-in-law of the [[Joseon Dynasty]]'s 7th King [[Sejo of Joseon]], and the son of [[Jeong In-ji]] (정인지).
His first wife was [[Princess Uisuk]](의숙공주), King [[Sejo of Joseon]]s younger daughter. His second wife was Lady Lee, General Yi jings daughter.
