{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]], [[Indian philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|20th century Philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Parvis Emad''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy|Continental]] |main_interests = [[Existentialism]], [[Heidegger]] |notable_ideas = |influences = |influenced = }}
'''Parvis Emad''' is an interpreter and translator of [[Martin Heidegger]]'s writings. He is the founder of, and a co-editor of, the journal ''[[Heidegger Studies]]'' and a professor of [[DePaul University]].<ref>[http://www.eudia.org/anni-precedenti/anno-4-2010/144-a-conversation-with-parvis-emad A Conversation with Parvis Emad]</ref> Emad is Iranian-born.<ref>[http://www.sooremag.ir/%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%82-dp22 انحلال روش در پرسش]</ref>
