In [[Roman Catholic]] [[theology]], '''Sententia certa''' refers to teachings without final approval but clearly deduced from revelation.<ref>''Fundamentals of Catholic dogma'' b Ludwig Ott, 1964, Herder, ASIN: B002BZOUAI pages 9-10</ref> These are below the [[Sententia fidei proxima]] level, but above [[Sententia communis]].

